<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122a102e-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1343"><num value="1343">§ 1343.</num><heading> Statistical Abstract of the United States</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to the usual number of the Statistical Abstract of the United States, twelve thousand copies shall be printed: three thousand for the Senate, six thousand for the House of Representatives, and three thousand for distribution by the Secretary of Commerce.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122a102f-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1273">82 Stat. 1273</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id122a1030-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
